Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pop half the @garlic clove{4}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over the grated garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the garlic bread).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium heat.

Once hot, lay the @chorizo slices{50%grams} into the pan and fry until crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once crispy, transfer to a #plate{} covered in #kitchen paper{}. Set aside.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and pepper chunks to the (now empty) #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @smoked paprika{1%sachet} to the pan. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @boiled water{600%milliliters}(for the rice), @honey{1%tbsp} and the @chicken stock paste{20%grams}.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} onto the pan (or cover with foil). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the mashed garlic and @mayonnaise{32%grams}.

When the paella is nearly ready, bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the paella is cooked, stir through the @peas{120%grams}.

Stir in the lemon zest and squeeze in half the lemon juice.

Taste the rice and season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed.

Share your ultimate chicken paella between your #bowls{}. Drizzle over the garlic mayonnaise and crumble the crispy chorizo over the top.

Scatter over the @wild rocket{20%grams} and drizzle with the @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}(for the dressing).

Serve with garlic bread and any remaining lemon wedges on the side. Enjoy!